<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-625-011  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 625 011.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Nov 20 1990 v4 n40 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Multi-Ad Search organizes Mac art: electronic catalog finds bykeyword. (Multi-Ad Services Inc.) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Said, Carolyn.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Multi-Ad Services Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Multi-Ad Search (File management software) (Product introduction)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSearchingGraphic ArtsCatalogsFile Management.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Electronic catalog finds by keywordandM;By Carolyn SaidandM;Peoria, Ill.andP;  -- Multi-Ad Services Inc. is offering a cure for Mac userswhose disks are bulging with graphics images: Multi-Ad Search, an electroniccatalog for organizing and managing Mac art.andM;&quot;You can accumulate quite a library of slides in academia and in the medicalfield.andP;  It can be quite a feat to go through them,&quot; said beta-tester JohnRootenberg, senior vice president of The Computers in Medicine Corp. in NewOrleans.andP;  Rootenberg, who used Multi-Ad Search to catalog his library of24-bit color medical images, said he found the program &quot;simple, elegant andwell-designed.&quot;andM;To ship this month for $199, Multi-Ad Search lets users catalog up to 32,000images and index graphics from their hard disk, optical drive, CD-ROM driveor any other desktop-mounted storage medium.andP;  The program can catalog imagesin a variety of file formats, including PICT, TIFF, RIFF, MacPaint andEncapsulated PostScript.andM;Users can view thumbnail images and can search graphics by any combination ofkeyword, file name, file type, volume or date.andM;&quot;It's very convenient.andP;  You can double-click on a thumbnail and it will openthe full image without the application being present,&quot; Rootenberg said.andM;Multi-Ad Search can automatically catalog users' existing disks by file type,volume and file names.andP;  Users must manually enter keywords and descriptions.andM;This month, Multi-Ad will release a free utility for image suppliers so theycan add keywords and descriptions to their products.andP;  The company willinclude keywords and descriptions with its electronic clip-art compendiumsbeginning in January.andM;Multi-Ad Search can place images directly into Multi-Ad Creator andQuarkXPress via a Copy Reference command.andP;  Multi-Ad said it hopes to persuadeAldus Corp., Digital Technology Inc. and other developers to incorporate itsdocument-referencing approach.andM;The Multi-Ad Search catalog can be stored on a server for simultaneous accessby multiple users.andM;Multi-Ad Services Inc. is at 1720 W. Detweiller Drive, Peoria, Ill.andO;61615-1695.andP;  Phone (309) 692-1530; fax (309) 692-5444.andO;</TEXT></DOC>